sub_title: PhD Candidate | Internal Erosion Research Group | UBC Vancouver
summary:
I am a PhD candidate in the Department of Civil Engineering, University of British Columbia, Vancouver.  I am currently working on BC Hydro and NSERC funded project on internal erosion. I have designed and built a state-of-the-art Flexible-wall Permeameter to characterize internal instability in widely-graded soils.

https://internalerosion.civil.ubc.ca/members/
Google Scholar: https://bit.ly/3wvlBWa

I have
-2 years of research experience as Research Engineer in the Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering, National University of Singapore.
-2 years and 5 months of industrial experience as Assistant Manager (Geotechnical) in consultancy work for Highways. 
-thorough knowledge of the common field and laboratory geotechnical tests.
-experience in analysis, design, and review of shallow & deep foundations, high embankments, and reinforced earth structures. I have worked extensively in all stages of detailed engineering from the interpretation of basic documents to the production of design calculations.
